{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a0e1f2b3-0000-4000-8000-200000000001",
    "name": "my-brain",
    "description": "Local testing collection for the my-brain self-hosted memory stack.\n\nAll requests route through the Caddy gateway (`rest_base_url` on port 8080, `mcp_base_url` on port 3333) and require a Bearer token set in the `auth_token` environment variable.\n\nImport alongside `my-brain.postman_environment.json` and select the **my-brain (local)** environment before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{auth_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Orchestrator",
      "description": "REST endpoints exposed by the Node orchestrator service (proxied through Caddy on port 8080).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{rest_base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{rest_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Liveness probe. Returns service name, current mode (memory/full), SONA enabled flag, and UTC timestamp.\n\nExpected: 200 OK with `status: \"ok\"`."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{rest_base_url}}/health",
                  "host": ["{{rest_base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["health"]
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"service\": \"my-brain-orchestrator\",\n  \"mode\": \"memory\",\n  \"sonaEnabled\": true,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-20T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{rest_base_url}}/v1/status",
              "host": ["{{rest_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "status"]
            },
            "description": "Returns runtime configuration summary: mode, LLM model/endpoint, and whether the DB URL is configured.\n\nExpected: 200 OK. In `memory` mode the `llm.endpoint` field will be `null`."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK – memory mode",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{rest_base_url}}/v1/status",
                  "host": ["{{rest_base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["v1", "status"]
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"service\": \"my-brain-orchestrator\",\n  \"mode\": \"memory\",\n  \"llm\": {\n    \"model\": \"qwen3.5:0.8b\",\n    \"endpoint\": null\n  },\n  \"memory\": {\n    \"dbConfigured\": true\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Unauthorized (token sanity check)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{rest_base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{rest_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Sends the health request **without** the Authorization header to verify the gateway rejects unauthenticated traffic.\n\nExpected: 401 Unauthorized with `WWW-Authenticate: Bearer realm=\"my-brain\"`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "MCP Bridge",
      "description": "MCP (Model Context Protocol) endpoints exposed by mcp-proxy (proxied through Caddy on port 3333).\n\nThe SSE transport requires two steps:\n1. `GET /sse` — opens a persistent SSE stream; the server returns a `sessionId` in the first event. Save that value into the `mcp_session_id` environment variable.\n2. `POST /messages?sessionId={{mcp_session_id}}` — sends a JSON-RPC 2.0 request and receives the response on the SSE stream.\n\nPostman's built-in SSE support (v10.19+) can be used for the SSE request; alternatively use `curl -N` from the terminal.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Open SSE stream",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "text/event-stream"
              },
              {
                "key": "Cache-Control",
                "value": "no-cache"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{mcp_base_url}}/sse",
              "host": ["{{mcp_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["sse"]
            },
            "description": "Opens the MCP SSE transport stream. The first event contains the `sessionId` needed for subsequent `POST /messages` calls.\n\nEvent shape:\n```\ndata: {\"sessionId\": \"<uuid>\"}\n```\n\nCopy the `sessionId` value into the `mcp_session_id` environment variable, then use the message requests below.\n\n**curl equivalent:**\n```bash\ncurl -N -H 'Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}' \\\n     -H 'Accept: text/event-stream' \\\n     http://127.0.0.1:3333/sse\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Initialize",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"method\": \"initialize\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"protocolVersion\": \"2024-11-05\",\n    \"capabilities\": {},\n    \"clientInfo\": {\n      \"name\": \"postman\",\n      \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n    }\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{mcp_base_url}}/messages?sessionId={{mcp_session_id}}",
              "host": ["{{mcp_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["messages"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sessionId",
                  "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "MCP JSON-RPC `initialize` handshake. Must be the first message sent on a new session.\n\nThe response is delivered on the SSE stream opened by `GET /sse`.\n\n**Prerequisite:** populate `mcp_session_id` from the SSE stream first."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List tools",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 2,\n  \"method\": \"tools/list\",\n  \"params\": {}\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{mcp_base_url}}/messages?sessionId={{mcp_session_id}}",
              "host": ["{{mcp_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["messages"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sessionId",
                  "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns the full list of tools registered by the ruvector MCP server.\n\nResponse arrives on the SSE stream. Inspect `result.tools` for available tool names and input schemas."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List resources",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 3,\n  \"method\": \"resources/list\",\n  \"params\": {}\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{mcp_base_url}}/messages?sessionId={{mcp_session_id}}",
              "host": ["{{mcp_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["messages"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sessionId",
                  "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns the list of resources exposed by the ruvector MCP server."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Call tool – store memory",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 4,\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"name\": \"store_memory\",\n    \"arguments\": {\n      \"content\": \"my-brain Postman test entry\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"source\": \"postman\",\n        \"tag\": \"test\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{mcp_base_url}}/messages?sessionId={{mcp_session_id}}",
              "host": ["{{mcp_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["messages"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sessionId",
                  "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Stores a memory entry via the ruvector MCP tool. Adjust `content` and `metadata` to match your test data.\n\nTool name may differ depending on the ruvector version — run **List tools** first to confirm the exact name."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Call tool – recall memory",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
